gures as Marinetti, Duchamp, Khlebnikov, and Vertov, and innovative contemporary artists like Viola, Wodiczko and Kac, The Force of Art counters the pessimism about art's social function by recovering and redefining art's transformative role in modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Aesthetics.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362484940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503624849423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503624849/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles